parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side
the ABS warning light comes on
the brakes grind loudly
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the ABS system fails to engage properly
the vehicle slides or lurches forward when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause reduced visibility during rain or snow, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers fail to turn on
wipers cut off during rain or light drizzle
wipers turn on and off intermittently
wipers stop working when the engine is hot
wipers only work when the engine is cold
tapping on the windshield wiper motor can temporarily restore function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A transmission fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a total loss, and can also pose a risk to the occupants' safety, as it can spread quickly and cause injuries.
symptoms: The transmission catches fire
resulting in flames and smoke coming from underneath the vehicle
potentially causing damage to the vehicle and surrounding areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed rear differential can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, as well as stranding the driver.

causing loss of power or control
unusual noises
or vibrations.

and potentially leading to transmission failure.
